      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(opencode-go): add qwen3.7-max, qwen3.7-plus, minimax-m3 to provider catalog",
        "body": "## Summary\nThis PR adds missing OpenCode Go provider catalog entries and implements tiered pricing for Qwen Plus models to ensure accurate cost estimation for long-context requests.\n\n### Changes\n- **New Models**: Added `minimax-m3`, `qwen3.7-max`, and `qwen3.7-plus` to the static provider catalog.\n- **Cost Accuracy**: Implemented `tieredPricing` for `qwen3.7-plus` and `qwen3.6-plus` to align with official OpenCode Go pricing (split at 256K tokens).\n- **Verification**: Added focused test cases in `extensions/opencode-go/index.test.ts` to verify cost calculations at the 256K boundary.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n### Run 1: qwen3.7-plus (Long Context)\n- **Model:** opencode-go/qwen3.7-plus\n- **Input Tokens:** 300,000\n- **Output Tokens:** 1,000\n- **Expected Cost:** 0.3648\n- **Actual Cost:** 0.3648\n- **Verdict:** ✅ Correct\n\n### Run 2: qwen3.6-plus (Long Context)\n- **Model:** opencode-go/qwen3.6-plus\n- **Input Tokens:** 300,000\n- **Output Tokens:** 1,000\n- **Expected Cost:** 0.6060\n- **Actual Cost:** 0.6060\n- **Verdict:** ✅ Correct\n\n### Run 3: qwen3.7-plus (Short Context)\n- **Model:** opencode-go/qwen3.7-plus\n- **Input Tokens:** 100,000\n- **Output Tokens:** 1,000\n- **Expected Cost:** 0.0416\n- **Actual Cost:** 0.0416\n- **Verdict:** ✅ Correct\n\nAll tests passed locally.",
